## Severity
Major
## Dimension
dry
## Location
src/vdd/mod.rs:209-281 (review_text) vs 348-398 (advisory_review)
## Violation
Both methods implement the same six-step pipeline: short-circuit on disabled/short input, run static analysis, build adversary request, send, parse findings, triage, format injection. The only difference is `review_text` accepts a `user_task: &str` directly while `advisory_review` extracts it from the original ChatCompletionRequest via `extract_user_task`.

The two paths must be kept in sync — for example, the recently-added (per the comments) static analysis flow runs in both, the triage layer ordering must match, and the genuine_count logging must match. Any drift between them creates two divergent VDD behaviors depending on which entry point the caller chose.

Compare line 241-280 (review_text) with 354-397 (advisory_review):
```rust
// review_text
let static_results = self.run_static_analysis().await;
let adversary_request = self.build_adversary_request(builder_text, user_task, &static_results, 1);
let (adversary_text, tokens_used) = self.send_to_adversary(&adversary_request).await?;
let mut findings = self.parse_findings(&adversary_text, 1);
self.triage_findings(&mut findings, &[], builder_text, builder_provider, builder_api_key).await;
let context_injection = format_findings_for_injection(&findings, &static_results);
```

```rust
// advisory_review — same six lines
let static_results = self.run_static_analysis().await;
let original_task = extract_user_task(original_request);
let adversary_request = self.build_adversary_request(builder_text, &original_task, &static_results, 1);
let (adversary_text, tokens_used) = self.send_to_adversary(&adversary_request).await?;
let mut findings = self.parse_findings(&adversary_text, 1);
self.triage_findings(&mut findings, &[], builder_text, builder_provider, builder_api_key).await;
let context_injection = format_findings_for_injection(&findings, &static_results);
```

## Mandated refactor
Extract the shared pipeline into one private method that takes the resolved `user_task: &str` (the only varying input). Both `review_text` and `advisory_review` become thin adapters: `review_text` calls the shared method with its arg directly; `advisory_review` calls `extract_user_task` first then delegates. Short-circuit checks (`!enabled`, `len < 100`) move into the shared method or a guard helper.

